Definition: computer science) a virtual drive that is created by setting aside part of the random-access memory to use as if it were a group of sectors
Example: access to a RAM disk is very fast but the data it contains is lost when the system is turned off
Synonyms: drive, random-access_memory, p, noun, cognition, computer_science, c, computer, science, a, virtual, that, is, created, by, setting, aside, part, of, the, random-access, memory, to, use, as, if, it, were, group, sectors, access, RAM, disk, very, fast, but, data, contains, lost, when, system, turned, off
Category: noun.artifact
